1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,433
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,800
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,133 --> 00:00:05,133
What?

4
00:00:05,300 --> 00:00:07,200
So he's been going around taking photos?

5
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:11,700
Not bad.

6
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,200
What are you doing?

7
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,349
Team Manager.

8
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:32,700
What is this?

9
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,477
Why are you going through my computer?

10
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,800
Well, I was just passing by,

11
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,400
and it was on, so...

12
00:00:39,579 --> 00:00:41,315
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, you're a repeat offender.

13
00:00:41,619 --> 00:00:43,109
What? A repeat offender?

14
00:00:43,109 --> 00:00:44,600
If not, what would you call it?

15
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:47,033
Trespassing into the CPO's office
and secretly photographing documents,

16
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:48,800
and now going through my computer.

17
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,133
Going through it?

18
00:00:50,653 --> 00:00:52,947
I barely touched it,
and the photos popped up,

19
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:54,700
so I just took a quick look.

20
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:57,400
Are you saying there's nothing wrong
with what you did?

21
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,200
No, that's not it, but...

22
00:01:01,233 --> 00:01:02,939
Can I be honest with you?

23
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:05,700
I joined the company,

24
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:07,800
but you haven't given any instructions
or held a single meeting,

25
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,976
and you're out on field work every day.

26
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:12,400
I keep wondering
when I'll actually get to work,

27
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:15,621
and what exactly you're doing.

28
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:19,389
So you were curious about what I do,

29
00:01:19,389 --> 00:01:21,700
and that's why you were looking
at your superior's computer...

30
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,248
without permission?

31
00:01:24,053 --> 00:01:25,917
Do you not understand basic conduct?

32
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:29,219
Do you think this is your playground
where you can run wild as you please?

33
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,709
Team Manager,
you're getting too worked up.

34
00:01:34,709 --> 00:01:35,600
Please stop.

35
00:01:36,433 --> 00:01:39,300
I'm sorry for overstepping,

36
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,709
but you left your "playground" unattended
like it's yours...

37
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:46,233
and neglected your staff...

38
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:48,433
I don't think you're in a position
to call me out.

39
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,800
What did you say?

40
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,100
I'm a developer.

41
00:01:51,633 --> 00:01:53,700
Regardless of it being
an orientation period,

42
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:55,933
if I can't even access the server,

43
00:01:55,933 --> 00:01:57,800
there's nothing I can do.

44
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,500
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

45
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,500
I just...

46
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:04,269
looked at a few photos
that appeared on the screen.

47
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:08,100
I didn't think
it was such a serious offense.

48
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:10,600
I'm sorry.

49
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:24,900
Why are you so angry?

50
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,900
Honestly, if I were in her position,

51
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:29,909
I'd be curious
about what you're thinking too.

52
00:02:29,909 --> 00:02:32,500
I'm still figuring things out myself,

53
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,435
and I'll start
once I've sorted my thoughts.

54
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,300
Can't she wait a little?

55
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,400
Then why not just say that?

56
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,400
Sorry for raising my voice in the office.

57
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,900
You don't have to apologize to me.

58
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,200
Gyeol! Han Gyeol!

59
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:21,700
Who is that? You made a friend?

60
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,300
She is younger than me.

61
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:27,433
Some kids were picking on her,
so I helped.

62
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:30,165
She's waiting for her mom over there.

63
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,333
I see. You're helping others now...

64
00:03:36,827 --> 00:03:38,300
You've all grown up.

65
00:03:40,233 --> 00:03:42,533
Come on, I made a reservation
for your birthday dinner.

66
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:43,700
Yes, Dad.

67
00:03:57,300 --> 00:04:01,400
I guess I still have a long way to go
before I'm fully grown, Dad.

68
00:04:14,139 --> 00:04:15,955
Was that really something
to get that mad about?

69
00:04:16,433 --> 00:04:17,633
It was just some photos.

70
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:24,033
That playground looked really familiar.

71
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:29,100
Let's just go home.

72
00:04:32,053 --> 00:04:33,533
Mister, could you throw this out?

73
00:04:33,533 --> 00:04:34,400
Yes.

74
00:04:38,533 --> 00:04:39,533
I'm sorry.

75
00:04:39,633 --> 00:04:41,040
Seriously...

76
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:42,300
I'm sorry.

77
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,500
Why you...

78
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,100
I'm sorry.

79
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,700
I'm sorry.

80
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:52,043
I'm sorry.

81
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:56,133
Why is she doing this again?

82
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:00,600
Mr. Han Ji Hun.

83
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,109
Throw away your own cup.

84
00:05:03,192 --> 00:05:05,500
What?

85
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:09,539
Why are you making someone else
deal with your cup?

86
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,952
Cho Eun Ae, aren't you going too far?

87
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,433
I told you not to speak casually.

88
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:17,933
Seriously.

89
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:23,300
Hey, don't tell me...

90
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:26,033
Don't tell you what?

91
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:28,400
You still haven't gotten over me,
have you?

92
00:05:30,029 --> 00:05:31,433
That's why you're acting like this, right?

93
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,100
What did you just say?

94
00:05:34,233 --> 00:05:36,700
This is ridiculous.

95
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:38,633
Listen.

96
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,000
Get a grip, okay?

97
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:46,500
Then...

98
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,933
did she become an intern because of me?

99
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,400
That sounds like something she'd do.

100
00:05:57,133 --> 00:05:59,200
What am I supposed to do with you?

101
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,300
Dad!

102
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,333
Bit Na.

103
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,664
Why are you so late?

104
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,533
I ended up having dinner...

105
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:14,600
with someone from the foundation.

106
00:06:14,933 --> 00:06:16,433
Did you eat something good?

107
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,433
Yes. Did you eat, Bit Na?

108
00:06:18,733 --> 00:06:22,264
Yes, Mom made curry and rice.
I just finished it.

109
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,100
How was the interview? Did it go well?

110
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,700
Bit Na, go brush your teeth.

111
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Okay.

112
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,600
The results are already out.

113
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,200
How?

114
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,200
Did you get it?

115
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,131
Tell me already. Did you or not?

116
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:49,200
I believe you'll understand me this time.

117
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,000
We argue sometimes,

118
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:56,400
but at our core,
we love and understand each other.

119
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:59,700
Yes. So what happened?

120
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:01,533
Honey,

121
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,133
I'm not taking the job.

122
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,700
Not taking it? What do you mean?

123
00:07:09,035 --> 00:07:10,400
Did the interview go well?

124
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:12,900
Should I call?

125
00:07:13,936 --> 00:07:17,133
No, she said not to tell...

126
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:23,731
- Hello?
- I'll be late tonight.

127
00:07:24,233 --> 00:07:25,833
I'm meeting a friend for drinks.

128
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:29,656
Okay, don't drink too much.

129
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,700
But which friend?

130
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:34,100
A high school friend.
You don't know him well.

131
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,433
Don't wait up. Bye.

132
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:43,133
Who is this high school friend?

133
00:07:46,064 --> 00:07:47,195
I'm home.

134
00:07:47,195 --> 00:07:48,733
Welcome back. You should eat.

135
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:51,433
No, I'm eating later with Cho Rong.

136
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:52,433
You don't have to make anything.

137
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:55,400
Are you two going to get drunk
on makgeolli again?

138
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,100
No, it's not like that.

139
00:07:59,557 --> 00:08:02,859
You work at a big company now.
What's with those clothes?

140
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,400
When did you get a suit?
It looks expensive.

141
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:09,648
Isn't that Eun Nim's suit
you spilled soy milk on last time?

142
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:12,733
No, my manager gave it to me as a gift.

143
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:14,633
Your manager? Why?

144
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:16,033
Why else?

145
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:19,133
Just a little "keep up the good work" gift
for a junior.

146
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,800
Is your manager a man?

147
00:08:22,433 --> 00:08:24,800
- No, a woman.
- Why would a woman...

148
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:27,033
You're more old-fashioned than I thought,
Mom.

149
00:08:27,033 --> 00:08:30,333
What? It's not common for a boss
to buy you clothes right after you join.

150
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:35,100
I thought maybe he liked you...

151
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:38,435
See, that mindset is outdated.

152
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:41,747
Fine, you're modern,
and I'm old-fashioned.

153
00:08:41,747 --> 00:08:42,747
Happy?

154
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:45,033
But you can't wear
that same outfit every day.

155
00:08:45,033 --> 00:08:46,533
Should I buy you something this weekend?

156
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,648
No, I have money.

157
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:51,075
I told you not to touch that lump sum.

158
00:08:51,252 --> 00:08:52,997
Don't even think about it.

159
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,633
Did she get a large sum of money?

160
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:58,133
Your sister got the full payout
from selling her company last time,

161
00:08:58,133 --> 00:09:01,100
a whopping 250,000 dollars all at once.

162
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:02,100
Really?

163
00:09:03,033 --> 00:09:04,749
And you're just keeping quiet about it?

164
00:09:04,749 --> 00:09:06,768
Don't even think about touching it.

165
00:09:07,933 --> 00:09:10,120
Once you start spending a lump sum...

166
00:09:10,856 --> 00:09:12,533
Do people earn money just to let it sit?

167
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:14,368
I'll go change and visit Cho Rong.

168
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:17,000
A big company and a good boss.

169
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:18,133
You won't find that easily.

170
00:09:18,133 --> 00:09:21,000
Make sure you become a full-time employee,
okay?

171
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:22,433
Here.

172
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,300
I made a mistake this time.

173
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,100
I'll look into something more solid soon.

174
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,833
No, you don't have to.

175
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,400
Over the past year,

176
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:40,312
I've had countless interviews,
and they all said the same thing.

177
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:43,277
At my age,

178
00:09:43,277 --> 00:09:46,033
I'll just be satisfied
doing what I can now.

179
00:09:46,033 --> 00:09:48,500
But you're wasting your abilities here.

180
00:09:49,272 --> 00:09:50,400
I'll keep looking...

181
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,400
Gwon Sik.

182
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:55,633
When I first met you
at Kangsu Construction,

183
00:09:56,800 --> 00:10:00,300
I'm sorry for asking
why you were with Dae Chi.

184
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,600
Why?

185
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,733
I know what it meant too.

186
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,000
In a way, we're in the same situation.

187
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,400
We're the heads of our families.

188
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,833
So what does it matter where we work?

189
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:18,000
Honestly,

190
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:22,000
I was pretty surprised
to see you in a cleaning uniform.

191
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:24,400
But when you put it that way,

192
00:10:25,633 --> 00:10:28,100
thinking like that in the first place
makes no sense.

193
00:10:30,885 --> 00:10:33,000
You seemed a bit uncomfortable
around Dae Chi.

194
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:34,733
- Are you okay?
- It's just...

195
00:10:36,643 --> 00:10:38,133
We never really got along.

196
00:10:40,233 --> 00:10:42,500
The Chairman even had us
take tutoring together...

197
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,552
to help Dae Chi settle down,

198
00:10:44,552 --> 00:10:45,833
and he tried really hard.

199
00:10:48,501 --> 00:10:51,033
I feel bad toward him.

200
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,700
Still, I remember...

201
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,900
you two being quite close.

202
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,600
Us?

203
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:07,633
Right.
Let's just leave the past in the past.

204
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:10,800
What do you mean?

205
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:13,400
You want Seong Jun by your side?

206
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:16,000
Yes, exactly.

207
00:11:16,549 --> 00:11:18,200
Just like Gwon Sik is by your side,

208
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:20,816
I'd like someone like that by mine.

209
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:23,700
Did you check what he wants?

210
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,733
Not yet.

211
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:30,600
But why not Mr. Ju or Mr. Seo?

212
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:33,651
Yong Man is more like someone
who keeps me in check,

213
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:34,800
and Gwon Sik...

214
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,500
He has no intention of being loyal to me.

215
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,395
I need someone I can truly trust...

216
00:11:41,395 --> 00:11:42,900
and who is capable, someone who's mine.

217
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,633
If you really need him,

218
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,592
win his heart first.

219
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,500
Are you okay, Father?

220
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:56,700
Honey! What's wrong?

221
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,900
Please go back to the hospital.

222
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:05,000
And step away from work.

223
00:12:06,033 --> 00:12:08,100
I can't step away!

224
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:11,900
You should go now. He's tired.

225
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:14,833
I'll be going.

226
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:22,233
He seems to be getting worse.

227
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,048
I'm really worried.

228
00:12:25,033 --> 00:12:28,160
Exactly. If he stays in the hospital,

229
00:12:28,357 --> 00:12:30,600
they can respond quickly in emergencies.

230
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,000
But being in the hospital...

231
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,000
won't change much. That's why.

232
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:36,833
What about a nursing hospital?

233
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:38,233
Or hospice care?

234
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:40,000
It's not at that stage yet,

235
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:43,133
but if his condition gets worse...

236
00:12:43,133 --> 00:12:44,760
It'll affect the stock price.

237
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:46,140
Of course.

238
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,000
And he says
he still has many things to do.

239
00:12:49,923 --> 00:12:51,403
Things to do?

240
00:12:51,403 --> 00:12:53,900
These days,
aside from spending time with Mother,

241
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,033
he doesn't seem to do much.

242
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:57,800
Even if he doesn't go to the office,

243
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,300
he oversees everything
like it's in his palm.

244
00:13:00,633 --> 00:13:02,035
Whatever.

245
00:13:02,261 --> 00:13:03,600
With things like this at home,

246
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:06,033
I feel suffocated these days.

247
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:10,309
So that's why you've been going dancing?

248
00:13:10,309 --> 00:13:12,165
If I don't do something like that,
how am I supposed to live?

249
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,700
I went out to relieve stress,

250
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:17,733
but ended up meeting a ridiculous woman
and got even more stressed.

251
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:20,683
Just wait, next time...

252
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:23,433
I'll put her in her place.

253
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:25,333
Don't go around saying who you are.

254
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:29,571
It'll turn into headlines
about abuse of power. Got that?

255
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:31,333
So should I just keep taking it?

256
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,633
Me?

257
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,907
That team manager...

258
00:13:37,907 --> 00:13:40,000
He's always out on field work,
taking photos.

259
00:13:40,433 --> 00:13:41,891
He shows up for ten seconds and leaves.

260
00:13:41,891 --> 00:13:43,500
Totally reckless.

261
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:45,200
Does being rich excuse everything?

262
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:48,261
Fine, he can slack off if he wants.

263
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,045
But at least share the server with me...

264
00:13:50,045 --> 00:13:52,133
so I can get my work done.

265
00:13:52,133 --> 00:13:53,233
Seriously.

266
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,851
Such a slippery, power-hungry jerk.

267
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,200
You're having a hard time, aren't you?

268
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:03,059
Yeah, I really am.

269
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,491
I guess they underestimated me...

270
00:14:05,491 --> 00:14:06,933
just because I accepted the intern offer.

271
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:09,300
Should I just quit tomorrow?

272
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:12,112
Yeah!
You've got the investment secured anyway.

273
00:14:12,251 --> 00:14:13,875
Yeah, just quit.

274
00:14:14,268 --> 00:14:15,268
Let's do that.

275
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:20,933
Seriously, I'll just...

276
00:14:21,733 --> 00:14:22,900
Grandma.

277
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,300
Quit?

278
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:29,869
There's a limit to taking things
for granted.

279
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:35,979
Do you know
how much your mom worried about you?

280
00:14:35,979 --> 00:14:38,200
And you're already talking about quitting?

281
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:41,433
You got into a big company,

282
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:44,400
and she thought
she could finally rest easy,

283
00:14:44,533 --> 00:14:46,200
and now you want to cause trouble again?

284
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:49,100
Grandma, Eun Ae wouldn't act like this
for no reason.

285
00:14:49,233 --> 00:14:51,500
Parents, while raising their children,

286
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:55,600
go through things
dozens of times worse than that,

287
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:58,033
working day and night...

288
00:14:58,033 --> 00:14:59,933
just to feed, clothe, and raise them.

289
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:03,485
I know, I was just saying it out of anger.

290
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,000
I'm sorry, Grandma.

291
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,200
Go home! You have work tomorrow.

292
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Yes, Grandma.

293
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:12,400
Good night. Bye, Cho Rong.

294
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,400
Bye.

295
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,900
(Kangsu Construction)

296
00:15:17,127 --> 00:15:18,160
Good morning, Team Manager.

297
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:20,100
Yes.

298
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,533
You're early again today.

299
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:23,700
Would you like some coffee?

300
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,900
Sure.

301
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:28,900
Please wait a moment.

302
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,033
Thank you.

303
00:15:38,033 --> 00:15:40,100
About yesterday...

304
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:41,800
I'm sorry.

305
00:15:42,221 --> 00:15:44,800
I'll be more careful from now on.

306
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:49,533
Good morning.

307
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:51,200
Good morning.

308
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:01,045
By the way, there's a team dinner tonight.

309
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,773
A team dinner?

310
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:04,925
I might finally feel like I belong.

311
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:07,933
Is it mandatory?

312
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:11,000
Of course. It's a welcome party
for you and the new hires.

313
00:16:11,233 --> 00:16:12,600
You can't miss it.

314
00:16:16,933 --> 00:16:18,333
That rude punk.

315
00:16:19,357 --> 00:16:23,033
Endure it.
Just until I pull my Joy out of this.

316
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:25,700
What's this?

317
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,333
(Weekly Top Ten, "The ER Witch,"
Total views, 200,000)

318
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:28,833
Why did the views...

319
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:31,433
suddenly increase so much?

320
00:16:34,933 --> 00:16:35,933
What? 12,000 dollars?

321
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:36,900
(Deposited to Cho Eun Nim, 12,000 dollars)

322
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:39,755
Did I actually make money
from my web novel?

323
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,233
Is this real?

324
00:16:48,733 --> 00:16:50,133
What should I do first with this money?

325
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:52,300
Right, Mom and Dad's trip...

326
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:53,933
No, wait.

327
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:57,000
What if they ask
where the money came from?

328
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:07,600
Please...

329
00:17:13,933 --> 00:17:14,933
(Preliminary results announcement)

330
00:17:14,933 --> 00:17:15,933
Yeah.

331
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:19,528
It's just preliminaries, I'll pass.

332
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,000
So nervous.

333
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:28,900
Wait.

334
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:31,133
I can do this.

335
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:32,733
- Seo Seung Wu.
- Please!

336
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,200
Why? Are the results out?

337
00:17:36,851 --> 00:17:38,133
I can't look.

338
00:17:41,162 --> 00:17:42,162
Come on.

339
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:44,000
Did you fail the preliminaries?

340
00:17:44,947 --> 00:17:47,200
That can't be...

341
00:17:50,433 --> 00:17:52,900
You said you had a good feeling.

342
00:17:53,613 --> 00:17:57,300
Well, better this than failing later.

343
00:17:57,700 --> 00:17:59,033
Better to get it over with sooner...

344
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:00,033
Mom!

345
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,800
Just give it up and find something else.

346
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
Something else? Like what?

347
00:18:05,233 --> 00:18:07,755
Comics are my destiny.

348
00:18:07,755 --> 00:18:09,300
It's everything to me!

349
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:11,300
Destiny, my foot.

350
00:18:11,861 --> 00:18:14,100
If that were true,
you would've succeeded by now.

351
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:16,880
How can this be?

352
00:18:17,272 --> 00:18:19,365
How?

353
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:25,275
You've done enough already.

354
00:18:26,033 --> 00:18:28,675
Like they say, "You lost but fought well."

355
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:31,856
Who says that?

356
00:18:31,856 --> 00:18:33,856
I've never even properly fought.

357
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:35,700
At least it's done.

358
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,900
Since it's all fallen apart,

359
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:41,312
just give it up and move on.

360
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,432
I'm going to exercise. Eat well.

361
00:18:44,432 --> 00:18:45,600
You failed again.

362
00:18:48,433 --> 00:18:50,500
This can't be.

363
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,500
This is betrayal.

364
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:54,700
- Good work, everyone.
- Good work.

365
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,869
- Good work.
- Good work.

366
00:18:57,133 --> 00:19:00,500
It seems this quarter's members
are especially enthusiastic.

367
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:01,733
It really energizes me.

368
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,200
Especially you two.

369
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,633
See you next class.

370
00:19:05,633 --> 00:19:08,749
- Good work.
- Thank you.

371
00:19:09,533 --> 00:19:10,533
Excuse me.

372
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:12,733
Enthusiasm is great,

373
00:19:13,133 --> 00:19:15,400
but how about dressing the part?

374
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,000
What?

375
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,000
You mean dancewear?

376
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,733
We're just exercising. Sweats are fine.

377
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,963
Do we really have to dress up like that?

378
00:19:24,963 --> 00:19:26,731
Well, why not look the part?

379
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:29,933
Don't you feel like you stand out?

380
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:32,100
Not at all.

381
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,100
Let's go get changed.

382
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,100
Wait.

383
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,733
Excuse me.

384
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:42,584
I'm curious.

385
00:19:43,433 --> 00:19:46,300
What do you do? Are you a homemaker?

386
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,400
Me?

387
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:53,833
Here.

388
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:55,500
You even have a business card?

389
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:57,000
(Our Happy Days Real Estate Office,
Licensed Realtor Kang Yeon Ja)

390
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,184
You're a licensed realtor.

391
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,533
A real estate lady?

392
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:06,566
It's usually called a licensed realtor.

393
00:20:06,904 --> 00:20:08,200
You didn't know?

394
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:10,500
What? Seriously...

395
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:13,819
Hey, do you know who I am?

396
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:18,300
Do I need to? Who are you?

397
00:20:18,445 --> 00:20:19,500
You should stop.

398
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:22,000
You see...

399
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,900
Let's go, Min Ho's mom.

400
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,600
So you're Min Ho's mom.

401
00:20:27,533 --> 00:20:29,633
All right, Min Ho's mom.

402
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,000
I'm fuming.

403
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:35,669
I don't care
if they call it abuse of power.

404
00:20:35,669 --> 00:20:38,253
I can't take this.
I'm not putting up with this.

405
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,789
Your glasses are empty? Good.

406
00:20:46,789 --> 00:20:48,633
- Here, a round for everyone.
- She's copying what she's seen.

407
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,300
No, Eun Ae...

408
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,100
Ms. Cho Eun Ae...

409
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:54,000
was our department's mixologist.

410
00:20:54,433 --> 00:20:56,400
A master of making bomb shots.

411
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,933
Everyone, take your glasses.

412
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:02,733
Now,
a toast from the Chief Planning Officer.

413
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:05,100
I'm not great at this.

414
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:06,900
All right.

415
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:13,900
To the bright future...

416
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:15,600
of Kangsu Construction's
retirement community TF.

417
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:16,899
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

418
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,272
This is it.

419
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:28,233
Team Manager, you like abalone, right?

420
00:21:28,233 --> 00:21:29,300
Enjoy.

421
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:30,300
Thanks.

422
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,500
You know his tastes too?

423
00:21:33,757 --> 00:21:35,200
Who doesn't like abalone?

424
00:21:36,789 --> 00:21:39,333
Abalone. Nice.

425
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:40,900
Looks good.

426
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:47,133
There's sea cucumber too.

427
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:50,600
Nice, I like that.

428
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:58,433
Enjoy, Team Manager.

429
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,000
Enjoy.

430
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,891
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, you seem to drink well.

431
00:22:04,233 --> 00:22:05,533
I'll pour you some.

432
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:07,949
Of course, it's an honor.

433
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:11,233
Thank you.

434
00:22:15,933 --> 00:22:17,633
How's work? Is it manageable?

435
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,701
Well, I'd like to work,

436
00:22:21,701 --> 00:22:24,533
but I don't have anything to do,
so I'm not sure.

437
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:28,896
The Team Manager must have plans.
Just wait.

438
00:22:29,633 --> 00:22:30,824
I'll pour you a glass too.

439
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,500
My role model is offering.

440
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,693
I can't refuse.

441
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:37,833
Role model? Me?

442
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:41,300
Yes, you're capable and charismatic,

443
00:22:41,613 --> 00:22:43,901
and endlessly warm to your team.

444
00:22:43,901 --> 00:22:46,300
You're my idol.

445
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:54,700
Don't overdo it.

446
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:58,579
No, I'm not.

447
00:22:58,864 --> 00:23:00,859
I've been idle for too long,

448
00:23:01,085 --> 00:23:03,900
so I'd like to go all out
at least at this dinner.

449
00:23:05,653 --> 00:23:07,613
Would you like a drink?

450
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:09,533
No, thank you.

451
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:14,133
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, that's enough.

452
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:16,541
Why do you care?

453
00:23:16,541 --> 00:23:19,300
Mixing drinks doesn't suit her.

454
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:20,600
Why not?

455
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:23,200
You said she was a mixology master.

456
00:23:24,333 --> 00:23:26,933
She made them. She didn't drink them.

457
00:23:26,933 --> 00:23:28,200
Shut it.

458
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:35,600
I wish I were on Team One.

459
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,700
I really want to work.

460
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,100
I need to pull the program out
as soon as possible...

461
00:23:42,100 --> 00:23:44,700
so I can leave this place.

462
00:23:58,233 --> 00:24:03,933
<i>This is the real deal</i>

463
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:08,251
<i>The real one's here</i>

464
00:24:09,152 --> 00:24:10,700
<i>Right now</i>

465
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:16,500
<i>This is the real deal</i>

466
00:24:17,539 --> 00:24:21,800
<i>I'll love you deeply</i>

467
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:25,233
Next, our Chief Planning Officer.

468
00:24:25,233 --> 00:24:26,833
Okay. Stay where you are.

469
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:29,624
- I'll go.
- Ko Min Ho!

470
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,600
Good work.

471
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:34,300
Number 62185.

472
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:36,749
- Number 62185.
- Number 62185.

473
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:44,500
<i>Can't I love you?</i>

474
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:46,000
Ko Min Ho.

475
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:51,033
<i>I can't help how I feel</i>

476
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:53,000
Ko Min Ho.

477
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:58,700
<i>You made me laugh and cry</i>

478
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:05,300
<i>But I was happy</i>

479
00:25:06,933 --> 00:25:10,000
Next, Manager Seo Seung Ri.

480
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:15,000
- Seo Seung Ri.
- Seo Seung Ri.

481
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,100
- Seo Seung Ri.
- You should sing.

482
00:25:29,688 --> 00:25:34,600
<i>Leave my life alone</i>

483
00:25:35,333 --> 00:25:39,488
<i>Don't interfere anymore</i>

484
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:43,816
<i>I'll live my own way</i>

485
00:25:45,233 --> 00:25:46,633
I knew it, Cho Eun Ae.

486
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:50,600
I'm going to be reborn.

487
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,200
What are you doing, Mr. Han Ji Hun?

488
00:25:53,091 --> 00:25:55,900
When Eun Ae's drunk,
she tends to drop things everywhere.

489
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,664
I'm just picking them up.

490
00:25:59,397 --> 00:26:01,493
You really care about your junior.

491
00:26:02,557 --> 00:26:05,033
This punk faked a kiss and scammed her?

492
00:26:05,033 --> 00:26:07,700
<i>I'll do what I want</i>

493
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:10,368
<i>I'll spread my wings</i>

494
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:14,833
<i>I have to be the owner</i>

495
00:26:14,833 --> 00:26:17,200
<i>Of my own life</i>

496
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,400
Applause.

497
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,133
Good job, sit down.

498
00:26:23,933 --> 00:26:24,933
This way.

499
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,333
Next, Team Manager Ko Gyeol.

500
00:26:28,333 --> 00:26:30,300
No, I can't sing.

501
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:36,000
- Sing.
- Sing.

502
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:38,533
What's wrong with you?
I really don't know any songs.

503
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:43,433
- Sing.
- Sing.

504
00:26:43,433 --> 00:26:44,600
Fine.

505
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,069
I'll sing.

506
00:26:47,933 --> 00:26:49,333
What number? Tell me.

507
00:26:49,833 --> 00:26:51,211
I'll sing a cappella.

508
00:26:57,433 --> 00:27:04,200
<i>On the way to Mom's work</i>

509
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:09,000
<i>White wild rose</i>

510
00:27:09,933 --> 00:27:16,633
- <i>The white petals of the wild rose</i>
- <i>The white petals of the wild rose</i>

511
00:27:16,633 --> 00:27:22,033
- <i>Taste good too</i>
- <i>Taste good too</i>

512
00:27:23,133 --> 00:27:30,355
- <i>On hungry days</i>
- <i>On hungry days</i>

513
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:36,021
- <i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>
- <i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

514
00:27:37,233 --> 00:27:43,435
- <i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>
- <i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>

515
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:48,600
- <i>I ate them</i>
- <i>I ate them</i>

516
00:27:50,437 --> 00:27:55,600
<i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>

517
00:27:56,357 --> 00:28:00,800
<i>I ate them</i>

518
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:09,733
(Our Happy Days)

519
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,805
If you're Ko Gyeol,

520
00:28:11,805 --> 00:28:13,344
I'm Cho Eun Ae.

521
00:28:13,344 --> 00:28:15,400
A very, very good girl.

522
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:17,033
Good girl.

523
00:28:17,033 --> 00:28:19,432
- Mother...
- Did the interview results come out?

524
00:28:19,432 --> 00:28:20,700
I can't do it! I won't!

525
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:22,000
What should I do?

526
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,300
All right, quit.

527
00:28:24,033 --> 00:28:25,061
No...

528
00:28:25,061 --> 00:28:26,300
Go ahead. No!

529
00:28:26,300 --> 00:28:27,533
Go ahead. No!

530
00:28:27,533 --> 00:28:29,500
Go ahead. No!

531
00:28:29,900 --> 00:28:31,633
